Ex. No:  — Manipulation and Filtering of Lists, Dictionaries, and Tuples
Aim

To manipulate and filter lists, tuples, and dictionaries in Python.

Theory

Python data structures like list, tuple, and dictionary are used to store and process data efficiently.

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda / IDLE / Jupyter Notebook
•
Windows / Linux Operating System

Program
# List Manipulation
numbers = [10, 25, 30, 45, 60]

numbers.append(80)
numbers.remove(25)

even_numbers = [n for n in numbers if n % 2 == 0]

print("List after manipulation:", numbers)
print("Filtered even numbers:", even_numbers)

# Tuple Filtering
marks = (78, 85, 62, 90, 55)

high_marks = tuple(m for m in marks if m > 70)

print("Tuple values:", marks)
print("Filtered marks (>70):", high_marks)

# Dictionary Manipulation
student = {
    "name": "Ravi",
    "age": 20,
    "department": "AI&DS",
    "marks": 88
}

student["grade"] = "A"
student["marks"] = 92

filtered_student = {
    k: v for k, v in student.items() if k != "age"
}

print("Dictionary after manipulation:", student)
print("Filtered dictionary:", filtered_student)


Procedure
Open Python/Jupyter Notebook.
Create a list with values.
Add elements using append().
Remove elements using remove().
Filter even numbers using condition.
Create tuple and filter values.
Create dictionary with key-value pairs.
Update dictionary values.
Filter dictionary items.
Execute program and check output.


